araus ergebenden Brüche nicht wegsystematisieren, sondern als intellektuelle Stolpersteine herausarbeiten. Die Herausgeber erhoffen sich durch das Buch eine langanhaltende und fruchtbare Diskussion.  aPublic and private data centers can only accomplish their mission by sharing resources, distributing work, dealing together with university policy-makers, and applying flexible project management. Accordingly, the presentations given at the fall meeting of the ZKI focused on communication. The authors have decades of combined experience in running computing centers while harnessing the talents of young staff.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aData processing service centersxEnergy conservation. 0aData processing service centersxManagement. 4aData centers. 4aDatenbanken. 4aDienstentwicklung. 4aIT security. 4aIT-Sicherheit. 4aRechenzentren. 4adatabases. 4aservice development. 7aCOMPUTERS / Information Technology.2bisacsh1 aHotzel, Hartmut , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLeendertse, Jan , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchulz, Janne Chr. , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWimmer, Martin , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 avon Suchodoletz, Dirk , eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2016z978311070100508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2016z9783110485103oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Engineering, Computer Sciences 2016z9783110485110oZDB-23-DEI0 cEPUBz97831104589540 cprintz978311045888640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311045975340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110459753423Coveruhttps://www.degruyt